Drywall- We employ only professional drywall installers and our goal is deliver complete satisfaction to each and every client with the quality of our workmanship and our prompt, reliable service.

OGC - Ottawa General Contractors are leaders as Ottawa's design and build renovation experts. Specializing in home renovations, new and custom home construction as well as home design. Magnolia Construction prides itself on the ability to listen and anticipate wants and needs. That’s what makes us exceptional at customizing our services to the unique situation of each and every client. We guide your vision through the entire renovation process and ensure that we are on the same page as to the best way to achieve it.

Our team of designers and builders brings expertise in a wide variety of aspects in home remodelling, and our track record of customer satisfaction earns us repeat business and referrals. You’ll find us as attentive and courteous in customer service as in the remodelling work itself.

We’ve transformed many a kitchen in Ottawa, with renovations ranging from islands and new counter tops to knocking down walls and changing the entire dynamic to a more contemporary space. Our extensive experience in kitchen renovations means you’re getting highly skilled craftsmanship to execute an exquisite transformation. Our clients give us rave reviews and have great things to say about the renovations we’ve done for the kitchens and other living spaces.

Our bathroom renovations deliver quality results, on time and on budget. We’ll work with you to create an upgraded bathroom that makes you want to linger for a while, light a candle and relax. We’ve remodeled countless bathrooms in Ottawa homes, from counters and sinks to showers & tubs to tile floors. We leave no stone unturned when we executive a renovation, keeping your full satisfaction in mind at every measurement, cut and fitting.

Magnolia will transform your basement from “blah” to “wow.” We’ll work with you to design and deliver a functional, livable basement space that your family (or your tenant) will truly enjoy. We have a knack for translating visions into reality. Talk to Magnolia about how we can work together to build a dream basement. When it comes to basements there’s no need to aim low. You deserve the best quality renovation. Magnolia can make that happen.

profile:
Estra Flooring has been serving the Ottawa community with uncompromising quality and exceptional customer service in the flooring industry since 1971. Now in our second generation, we continue to combine old world artisanship with the latest in flooring technology, with a wide variety of styles and products to accommodate a vast spectrum of home and commercial décor.

Our portfolio includes a number of notable and prestigious projects including hardwood flooring at the main function room at Rideau Hall, 24 Sussex Drive, the Rideau Club, the Committee Room on Parliament Hill and all the hardwood flooring at the National Gallery of Canada including the Rideau Street Chapel which has been reassembled there as a permanent exhibit.

Pre-Finished and Unfinished Wood Installation - simple and complex installations.
Sanding and Staining - change the mood and color of your floors, or renew the look of worn out existing hardwood floors.

Screen and Coat - refresh the sheen and the glamour, removes existing finish replaces it for a much cleaner and fresher look.

Our specialties include:

Custom Hardwood including rare & exotic woods,

Solid & Engineered,

Laminates, Cork, Bamboo

Ceramic Tile, Glass Tile

Luxury Vinyl Tile

Carpet and Carpet Tile

Condo (sound absorbent) floors

Sales, Service, Custom Designs, Free on site Estimates.

Residential –  primarily our business comes from our valued residential clients. We offer the utmost in friendly and practical advice, making sure that whatever your budget, we can make your dreams come true.

Commercial – Estra Flooring has maintained special relationships with Ottawa’s most prestigious architects, designers, builders and agencies such as Ottawa Community Housing as a result of our goal to achieve the best result as dictated by our commercial partners' expertise.

From the Rideau Hall to your home, the service we provide is of unparalleled quality.

Please visit our showroom located at 439 Preston Street, Ottawa, Ontario K1S 4N5

Monday through Saturday, Office:  613-233-0149                          

At Estra Flooring the coffee and hospitality is always on!

profile:
General contractors specializing in decks and exterior structures.  All our decks start on a solid foundation of helical metal piles and 2x8 or 2x10 (depending on deck size) pressure treated framing lumber.  This ensures a strong and stable deck for decades to come.  We then work with our clients to determine whether pressure treated, cedar or composite decking is best for their application as well as the most appropriate railing system (where required) to use.  We always take care of all necessary permits and drawings required by the City of Ottawa. 

We carry full commercial liability insurance coverage and all of our employees are WSIB covered and fall arrest certified.  We also ensure that any subcontractor we bring onto your property also carries liability insurance and WSIB coverage so you can rest easy knowing that your property is in safe hands.  

So whether you're looking for a small deck to put the BBQ on, an elevated walkout to enjoy the view or a large scale backyard oasis, we have the knowledge and industry contacts to make it a reality!

We are a small team of experienced personnel who are devoted to making our clients happy. There is a great deal of satisfaction that is felt when a customer finally sees the job, completed to his/her exact specifications, and is left speechless and/or with a big smile on his/her face!

At Brickworkx, we are dedicated to doing things right the first time! Every job that we tackle is completed with the time and care that we would put into our own homes. We understand that to many individuals, your home is your castle. However, we DO NOT believe that a renovation or upgrade should cost an arm and a leg. We strive to provide fast, high quality service at extremely reasonable pricing. Remember: a higher price does not automatically guarantee quality workmanship. Brickworkx is able to provide lower pricing because as a small company, our overhead is also quite low. 

Brickworkx can offer the following services:

-Brick and Natural Stone (Masonry)
-Carpentry (Trim, Moldings, Doors, etc...)
-Concrete and Paving
-Countertops and Vanities
-Decks, Patios and Outdoor Living
-Demolition and Wall Removal
-Drywall and Texture
-Fencing
-Flooring and Carpeting
-Foundation Repair
-Insulation
-Landscape Design and Installation
-Mold Removal and Restoration
-Painting
-Plumbing
-Roofing
-Siding
-Tiling
-Tree Removal

If there is a service you require that isn't listed, feel free to contact us! No job is too big or too small. You can book an appointment and request a FREE, no obligation quote. That means we will drive to you, assess the job, and provide you with an estimate at no charge! We are a group of honest and hardworking individuals. We pride ourselves in the work we do. There is no better satisfaction than driving past a job you completed, and having it still look brand new 10 years later!

profile:
J&M Bourdeau Contracting was created because we felt clients deserved the best experience when it comes to home renovations. Other than buying a house, or a car, renovations can be the third largest financial decision someone (or a couple) will make. You deserve complete transparency and great quality of the final product.
With over 20 years combined customer service experience and 10 years of construction experience, we want you to feel at ease about your next project. 
We do things a little different:
So, here’s a few things we do differently than most other renovations companies. We don’t include materials in the price. 
You may say, WHAT?! WHY?!
The reason is to keep costs down for the client. Contractors will usually charge about 10-15% above the material cost to make that little extra profit. We don’t do that. 
Here is our process:
- We make the material list
- We price out the material
- You give us cash
- We get the material
- We give you the change and the receipt
It’s that simple. This also means when we get a discount, YOU get the discount also.
Something else we do differently is provided daily work logs. We do this because sometimes, it seems the project did not make a lot of progress a certain day. This allows us to tell you what we did, and what delays we may have encountered. Complete transparency.
